 Account Security....</span><hr size=1> Over the past few months I've seen numerous people saying they've been hacked and such.  While I will never say something is impossible, I'm familiar with the way VI and other places provide password protection.  Its not foolproof but it should be very difficult for people to simply &quot;hack&quot; their way into EQ.  <br>
<br>
Over 50% of the cases, a player wasn't hacked, they were simply careless with their log in info.  All it takes for someone to figure out a password if they have your log-in name is a lot of patience and extra time on their hands.  The sheer number of people who use passwords like 1111 or 1234 is staggering.  <br>
<br>
A vast majority of the remaining cases deals with people unwittingly giving out portions of their Log-in info.  Some tips for you and if you have done any of the following I STRONGLY urge you to log-in now and change your password immediately.<br>
<br>
1.  EQ sites that require you to login.  This includes the popular website known as Magelo and even EZ board here.  What a lot of people do not realize that while logging in the EQ Game is primarily secure, sites like EZ Board and the like may not be.  Any hacker with good enough experience can hack the login database and steal login info and people have a tendency to use the same login names and passwords.  This narrows down their search for your password considerably.<br>
<br>
2.  Get a firewall installed.   Anytime a person is connected to the internet, they are vulnerable.  A person can do any variety of things to your computer not the least of which is transmit programs to your computer that will send a copy of all the material your computer sends over the net.  An excellent firewall is available for free at Cnet downloads called Zonealarm.  I'd highly recommend trying it.<br>
<br>
3.  No matter who they are, unless you know them personally AND unless you know the person well, don't trust people with your login name.  Thats half your information right there.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Anyways, most people have the wrong idea about hacking.  As I said, while no system is full proof, you can help minimize your vulnerability to those who would try to steal your information from you.  <br>
<br>
<br>
